{"word":"βασκαίνω","slug":"βασκαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βασκαίνω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to slander, malign, belie, disparage</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <i>to envy, grudge</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to bewitch</i>, by means of spells: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ὡς μὴ βασκανθῶ</el> (aor1 <a href='S:subjunctive mood'>subj.</a>) that <i>I be</i> not <i>bewitched</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}